entries.title: The parade may have been called off but Argentinians will still celebrate into the early hours
entries.description: The streets of Buenos Aires were filled with millions of people, from the city centre all the way out to the motorway, as they hoped to catch a glimpse of Argentina's World Cup heroes.

entries.title: Zelenskyy set to meet Biden in US tomorrow - his first trip outside Ukraine since start of war
entries.description: Volodymyr Zelenskyy is set to travel to the United States to meet President Joe Biden at the White House tomorrow.

entries.title: Argentina's World Cup heroes fly over huge crowds after bus parade cancelled due to safety fears
entries.description: An open-air bus parade for Argentina's World Cup heroes had to be called off part-way through to protect the safety of millions of fans who had poured onto the streets of Buenos Aires.

entries.title: Taliban bans women from universities in Afghanistan
entries.description: Female students have been banned from universities in Afghanistan with immediate effect, the Taliban has said.

entries.title: 'A really kind, good guy': Teammate of Iranian footballer facing death penalty speaks out
entries.description: A former teammate of Iranian footballer Amir Nasr-Azadani, who faces the death penalty for participating in nationwide protests, has told Sky News that his friend is a "shy person" and "really kind".

entries.title: California earthquake leaves two people injured and tens of thousands without power
entries.description: At least two people have been injured and tens of thousands of homes and businesses left without power after a strong earthquake hit northern California.

entries.title: Lionel Messi beats egg with most-liked Instagram post ever
entries.description: He shoots, he scores... again. Lionel Messi has taken the lead for the most-liked post ever on Instagram, with a photo of him lifting the World Cup.

entries.title: 'We are dying': Desperate plea for help from Rohingya refugees stranded at sea for two weeks
entries.description: A number of people have reportedly died from starvation on a stranded boat, carrying 160 Rohingya refugees, which is adrift in Indian waters in the Andaman Sea.

entries.title: Argentina World Cup winners return home to Buenos Aires
entries.description: After taking the World Cup crown, Argentina returned home to Buenos Aires on Tuesday with the country declaring the day of celebration as a national holiday.
